data.text: @punchycritic @CountyOfVolusia Ugh, I’m sorry to hear that. This whole thing is a shit show. I haven’t heard people getting vaccinated here yet either so yeah, who knows when that will be.
@flickchickdc @CountyOfVolusia Sorry to hear that. The rollout of this vaccine has been embarrassing. I'm in phase 3 because I'm high-risk, and at this rate who knows when that'll be.

I get that there is a broader issue of available vaccine inventory, but the @CountyOfVolusia is thinking more critically (haha) about traffic patterns than triaging vaccine recipients in any meaningful way. Bottom line: my grandma is sad, I’m angry, & Volusia County can suck it.

Not only is that unacceptable and indicative of issues nationwide, the county is opening the vaccine administration to those 65+ and reassured that they don’t anticipate  traffic issues. Glad traffic is the main concern and not the health of the nation’s most vulnerable. 2/3
